				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">Well, 100,000's of plats is not that hard to come by legtimately so I dont think its going to be that obvious.   My average cash flow is about 40,000 pp a day (of course, just a small percentage of that is actual profit).  A good tradeskiller, or in my case a guild with alot of tradeskillers, can generate large amounts of cash in relatively shorts amount of time.  Just depends on how active you are and how willing you are to do alot of mindless clicking.
<br />

<br />
There are also alot of good merchants in the bazaar that know prices pretty well and can turn around items for a profit doing nothing but buying and selling.  Those guys can make thousands of plat a day.   I am going to parse my bazaar log and see how many plat I have made on my bazaar mule in the 270+ days he has set there.  Conservatively, I would say 20 million but thats a wild guess.<span class="gensmall"></span>


